---
const taglines = [
  "Patterns for AI-assisted engineering",
  "From vibes to systems",
  "Not faster. Better."
];
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta name="description" content="Fighting With AI - Patterns for AI-assisted software engineering" />
    <title>Fighting With AI</title>
    <style>
      * {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      body {
        font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
        background: #0a0a0a;
        color: #e5e5e5;
        min-height: 100vh;
        display: flex;
        align-items: flex-start;
        justify-content: center;
        padding: 10vh 1rem 4rem;
        overflow-x: hidden;
      }

      main {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 2rem;
        max-width: 700px;
      }

      .intro {
        margin-top: 4rem;
        text-align: left;
        color: #a3a3a3;
        line-height: 1.7;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
      }

      .intro p {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      }

      .intro ul {
        margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
      }

      .intro li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      }

      .intro strong {
        color: #e5e5e5;
      }

      .intro .big-idea {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        color: #e5e5e5;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 2rem 0;
        font-weight: 500;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 10vw, 5rem);
        font-weight: 800;
        letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff 0%, #a3a3a3 100%);
        -webkit-background-clip: text;
        -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
        background-clip: text;
        animation: fadeInUp 0.8s ease-out;
      }

      .tagline-container {
        height: 2rem;
        overflow: visible;
        position: relative;
      }

      .tagline {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        color: #737373;
        font-weight: 500;
        letter-spacing: 0.02em;
        position: absolute;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(20px);
        opacity: 0;
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      .tagline.active {
        animation: taglineFade 3s ease-in-out;
      }

      @keyframes fadeInUp {
        from {
          opacity: 0;
          transform: translateY(30px);
        }
        to {
          opacity: 1;
          transform: translateY(0);
        }
      }

      @keyframes taglineFade {
        0% {
          opacity: 0;
          transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(20px);
        }
        15%, 85% {
          opacity: 1;
          transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(0);
        }
        100% {
          opacity: 0;
          transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(-20px);
        }
      }

      .glow {
        position: fixed;
        width: 400px;
        height: 400px;
        border-radius: 50%;
        background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.15) 0%, transparent 70%);
        pointer-events: none;
        top: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
        animation: pulse 4s ease-in-out infinite;
      }

      @keyframes pulse {
        0%, 100% {
          opacity: 0.5;
          transform: translate(-50%, -50%) scale(1);
        }
        50% {
          opacity: 0.8;
          transform: translate(-50%, -50%) scale(1.1);
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="glow"></div>
    <main>
      <h1>Fighting With AI</h1>
      <div class="tagline-container">
        {taglines.map((line, i) => <span class="tagline" data-index={i}>{line}</span>)}
      </div>

      <div class="intro">
        <p>AI can write code and explain things, but it also makes mistakes and sounds confident when it's wrong.</p>

        <p>This is a collection of patterns for working with AI without letting it mess things up. "Fighting With AI" means:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Verifying its output</li>
          <li>Setting clear constraints</li>
          <li>Knowing when to trust it</li>
          <li>Staying in control</li>
        </ul>

        <p>The book covers three areas:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Concepts</strong> — AI and machine learning fundamentals that help you understand the technology you're working with.</li>
          <li><strong>Failure Modes</strong> — Dynamics that result in unreasonable or unmaintainable outputs from AI.</li>
          <li><strong>Patterns</strong> — Common techniques employed in practice to stay in control.</li>
        </ul>

      </div>
    </main>
    <script>
      const taglines = document.querySelectorAll('.tagline');
      let current = 0;

      function showTagline() {
        taglines.forEach(t => t.classList.remove('active'));
        taglines[current].classList.add('active');
        current = (current + 1) % taglines.length;
      }

      showTagline();
      setInterval(showTagline, 3000);
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
